@startuml
title Timebox 2 - Assignment Management Process

actor Teacher
actor Student

participant "Subject" as Subject
participant "Assignment" as Assignment
participant "Submission" as Submission

' --- Create & publish assignment ---

Teacher -> Subject: View assigned subjects
Subject --> Teacher: Show subject list

Teacher -> Assignment: Create assignment\n(subjectId, title, dueDate, maxScore, settings)
Assignment -> Assignment: Validate teacher assignment\nand input fields
Assignment --> Teacher: Confirm assignment saved\nstatus = draft

Teacher -> Assignment: Publish assignment\n(assignmentId)
Assignment -> Assignment: Update status\ndraft -> published
Assignment --> Teacher: Confirm published
Assignment --> Student: Assignment available\n(for enrolled students)

' --- Student submits work ---

Student -> Assignment: View assignment details
Assignment --> Student: Show details and\nsubmission status

Student -> Submission: Submit assignment\n(assignmentId, file, comments)
Submission -> Submission: Validate enrolment, file type\nand file size
Submission -> Submission: Create or update submission\nstatus = submitted
Submission --> Student: Confirm submission

' --- Teacher grades submission ---

Teacher -> Submission: View submissions\n(assignmentId)
Submission --> Teacher: List submissions\nwith students and files

Teacher -> Submission: Grade submission\n(submissionId, score, feedback)
Submission -> Submission: Validate score\n(0..maxScore)
Submission -> Submission: Save grade\nstatus = graded, set graded_at
Submission --> Teacher: Confirm graded

' --- Student views feedback ---

Student -> Submission: View my submission\nand feedback
Submission --> Student: Show file, score\nand feedback

@enduml